description:
Ecophi is digitializing the electrical grid. Our QMU 800 is a high-precision, software-defined merging unit used in modern digital substations. We’re looking for a hands-on engineer who loves low-level embedded programming, board bring-up, and working side-by-side with hardware to ship robust, real-time systems.

What you’ll do

Develop and optimize low-level firmware in C (bare-metal/RTOS) for data-acquisition, time-sync, and high-speed I/O on QMU 800.

Write device drivers (SPI, I²C, UART, Ethernet), DMA/ring buffers, and ISR-driven data paths for high-resolution ADCs.

Implement and harden substation protocols/time sync (e.g., IEC 61850 Sampled Values/GOOSE, PTP/IEEE 1588); contribute to PQ/PMU features.

**Board bring-up & hardware validation:** read schematics, probe signals, characterize performance with scopes/logic analyzers.

Collaborate with hardware on Altium Designer projects; review schematics/PCB layouts; suggest SI/PI-aware changes and test points.

Build automated tests, HW-in-the-loop rigs, calibration flows; contribute to CI and coding standards.



Must-haves

Solid experience with embedded C for microcontrollers/SoCs (interrupts, timers, peripherals, memory, concurrency);

**Comfortable with low-level debugging:** oscilloscopes, logic analyzers, JTAG/SWD, power measurements;

Very comfortable working in linux environments;

**Strong grasp of data acquisition basics:** ADCs, sampling theory, filtering, fixed- vs floating-point trade-offs;

Git-based workflows and disciplined engineering habits (reviews, documentation, reproducible builds).



Nice-to-haves

FPGA experience (VHDL/Verilog);

Altium Designer familiarity and the ability to read/modify schematics & PCB designs (basic layout understanding);

EMC/robustness for industrial gear (IEC 60255/61850-3), secure boot/DFU, factory test fixtures

Python for test automation; CMake; static analysis.



Why EcoPhi

Ecophi is a startup located in Gothenburg, founded by researchers at Chalmers University of technology. We have a deep technical core and strive to deliver solutions that are best in the industry.

Build cutting edge technological products used by leading utilities to modernize the grid;

Hardware lab with proper tools, real field feedback, and fast iteration;

Competitive pay, stock options, flexible work, and big ownership over your domain.



**How to apply:** Send your CV/LinkedIn, transcript and a short note about a low-level project you’re proud of (what you optimized, how you measured it) to jakob@ecophi.ai with the subject “Embedded Engineer — QMU800”.
